  "prompt": "Since each of us has been a student first, what is the harshest thing a teacher taught you?",
  "response": "One of the harshest lessons many students learn from teachers is the importance of accountability and the consequences of one's actions. A particular instance might be a teacher assigning a challenging project with a strict deadline, emphasizing that late submissions would receive no credit. This can be a tough lesson for students who underestimate the time needed or fail to manage their priorities effectively. While it may feel harsh in the moment, it often teaches valuable skills such as time management, responsibility, and the importance of following through on commitments\u2014lessons that extend far beyond the classroom.",
